  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How do I get an internship at IITs in December?",
  "response": "Getting an internship at the Indian Institutes of Technology (IITs) in December involves several steps. Here\u2019s a guide you can follow:\n\n1. **Know the Requirements**: Research specific IITs that you are interested in. Different IITs may have varying internship requirements, deadlines, and application procedures.\n\n2. **Decide on Your Area of Interest**: Identify your field of study or the department you wish to intern in. This could be Computer Science, Mechanical Engineering, Electrical Engineering, etc.\n\n3. **Prepare Your Documents**:\n   - **Resume**: Highlight your academic achievements, skills, relevant projects, and any prior experience. Make it concise and clear.\n   - **Cover Letter**: Write a tailored cover letter for each application explaining your interest in the internship and why you want to work at that particular IIT.\n   - **Transcripts**: Have your academic transcripts ready if required.\n\n4. **Look for Opportunities**:\n   - **IIT Official Websites**: Many IITs have dedicated internship portals or career services sections. Check these for postings about internships.\n   - **Faculty Contacts**: Reach out to faculty members whose work aligns with your interests. You can often find their contact details on the department\u2019s website. A well-crafted email asking for internship opportunities can open doors.\n   - **Networking**: Attend workshops, seminars, and other events at IITs, or connect with students and alumni on platforms like LinkedIn to learn about opportunities.\n\n5. **Apply Early**: December internships may have application deadlines in the preceding months. Make sure to apply well in advance.\n\n6. **Follow Up**: After submitting your application, it\u2019s appropriate to follow up with a polite email to express your continued interest.\n\n7. **Prepare for Interviews**: If selected for an interview, be ready to discuss your skills and how they relate to the internship role. Brush up on relevant technical knowledge and be prepared to discuss your projects.\n\n8. **Consider Other Platforms**: Use portals like Internshala, LinkedIn, or specific career services websites for internship postings.\n\n9. **Stay Persistent**: Getting an internship can be competitive. If you don\u2019t succeed initially, keep applying and consider broadening your search to other institutions or companies.\n\nIf you're a student affiliated with an IIT, check if your institution has specific internship programs or tie-ups with companies for winter internships, as they can facilitate obtaining an internship more easily. Good luck!",
